ction. I=E2=80=99ve been thinking this was bound to happen all along, even =
when Zaz lost the NBA and people doubted he knew what he was doing. It=E2=
=80=99s clear now that Zaz is onto something. <br/><br/>Earlier this week, =
he cut a new carriage deal with Comcast that worked out far better for WBD =
than most people thought it would, especially since Roberts could have zing=
ed Zaz on carriage fees now that TNT lost its NBA rights. Instead, the two =
men worked out a deal that will probably serve both of them well. And now, =
with Thursday=E2=80=99s reorg, Zaz has made clear he=E2=80=99ll do
what=E2=80=99s necessary to reduce the sting of his declining linear TV bus=
iness and get WBD a much-desired credit-rating upgrade. And, boy, have equi=
ty investors responded. The WBD stock was up 15.4 percent on Thursday alone=
, and up 35 percent in the last month. The tide is beginning to turn. <br/>=
